<p>You can specify a format string for the post date here. If you leave it blank or if you enter something invalid, it will use the Full Date Time Pattern.</p>
<p>Examples of valid patterns:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>MMMM dd, yyyy</strong> (Displays as December 31, 2010)</li>
<li><strong>MMM dd, yyyy</strong> (Displays as DEC 31, 2010)</li>
<li><strong>MM/dd/yyyy</strong> (Displays as 12/31/2010)</li>
<li><strong>dd/MM/yyyy</strong> (Displays as 31/12/2010)</li>
</ul>
